android.permission.READ_MEDIA_IMAGES.info: allows reading image files from external storage.
android.permission.READ_MEDIA_IMAGES.description: Allows an application to read image files from external storage.

android.permission.CAMERA.description: Allows application to take pictures and videos with the camera. This allows the application to collect images that the camera is seeing at any time.

android.permission.READ_MEDIA_VISUAL_USE.info: allows reading user-selected image or video files from external storage.
android.permission.READ_MEDIA_VISUAL_USE.description: Allows an application to read image or video files from external storage that a user has selected via the permission prompt photo picker. Apps can check this permission to verify that a user has decided to use the photo picker, instead of granting access to READ_MEDIA_IMAGES or READ_MEDIA_VIDEO . It does not prevent apps from accessing the standard photo picker manually. This permission should be requested alongside READ_MEDIA_IMAGES and/or READ_MEDIA_VIDEO , depending on which type of media is desired.

android.permission.READ_CALENDAR.description: Allows an application to read all of the calendar events stored on your phone. Malicious applications can use this to send your calendar events to other people.

android.permission.WRITE_CALENDAR.info: add or modify calendar events and send emails to guests
android.permission.WRITE_CALENDAR.description: Allows an application to add or change the events on your calendar, which may send emails to guests. Malicious applications can use this to erase or modify your calendar events or to send emails to guests.

android.permission.WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAG.description: Allows an application to write to external storage.

android.permission.WAKE_LOCK.description: Allows an application to prevent the phone from going to sleep.

android.permission.RECEIVE_BOOT_COMPLETE.description: Allows an application to start itself as soon as the system has finished booting. This can make it take longer to start the phone and allow the application to slow down the overall phone by always running.

android.permission.FOREGROUND_SERVICE.info: enables regular apps to use Service.startForeground.
android.permission.FOREGROUND_SERVICE.description: Allows a regular application to use Service.startForeground.

com.google.android.c2dm.permission.RECEI.description: Allows an application to receive push notifications from cloud.

android.permission.ACCESS_ADSERVICES_ATT.info: allow applications to access advertising service attribution
android.permission.ACCESS_ADSERVICES_ATT.description: This enables the app to retrieve information related to advertising attribution, which can be used for targeted advertising purposes. App can gather data about how users interact with ads, such as clicks or impressions, to measure the effectiveness of advertising campaigns.

android.permission.ACCESS_ADSERVICES_AD_.info: allow app to access the device's advertising ID.
android.permission.ACCESS_ADSERVICES_AD_.description: This ID is a unique, user-resettable identifier provided by Google's advertising services, allowing apps to track user behavior for advertising purposes while maintaining user privacy.

com.google.android.finsky.permission.BIN.description: A custom permission defined by Google.

android.permission.CHANGE_WIFI_MULTICAST.description: Allows an application to receive packets not directly addressed to your device. This can be useful when discovering services offered nearby. It uses more power than the non-multicast mode.

android.permission.READ_PHONE_STATE.description: Allows the application to access the phone features of the device. An application with this permission can determine the phone number and serial number of this phone, whether a call is active, the number that call is connected to and so on.

manifest_findings.title:
Clear text traffic is Enabled For App
[android:usesCleartextTraffic=true]
manifest_findings.description: The app intends to use cleartext network traffic, such as cleartext HTTP, FTP stacks, DownloadManager, and MediaPlayer. The default value for apps that target API level 27 or lower is "true". Apps that target API level 28 or higher default to "false". The key reason for avoiding cleartext traffic is the lack of confidentiality, authenticity, and protections against tampering; a network attacker can eavesdrop on transmitted data and also modify it without being detected.
manifest_findings.name: Clear text traffic is Enabled For App [android:usesCleartextTraffic=true]

3. Wenn Sie Fragen haben, wenden Sie sich bitte per E-Mail an das DanceFitMe-Team: support@dancefit.me."

playstore_details.title: Dancefitme: Fun Workouts
playstore_details.description:
DanceFitme provides energetic dance workouts and cardio for weight loss everywhere! Get motivated with hip-hop-inspired fitness and our exclusive 4-week workout plans. Sweat and have fun with Dancefitme which contains workouts from beginner to advanced with popular music!

WITH DanecFitme YOU’LL GET:
- Get an exclusive 28-day personalized dance challenge, start anywhere and anytime
- Connect your dance workouts directly to your TV Experience to enjoy a higher-quality experience
- Hip-hop, aerobics, jazz, Latin, salsa, Kpop, walking dance, and other dance styles, make exercising easy and enjoyable
- Become slim, sexy, and happy all in just one app

Dance Workouts Styles include: 
>> Aerobics
>> Dance Fitness
>> Hiphop 
>> Salsa
>> K-pop
>> Jazz
>> Latin
>> Walking Dance
and more to be explored...

Every small step counts for transforming your body, so start moving by downloading the DanceFitme app! 
- A dance workouts app for weight loss
- Numerous beginner dance workouts for choosing freely
- Professional dancer team creates dance workouts and customizes the 28-day plan based on your fitness level
- Break a sweat with dance workouts at home 

🌟DanceFitme provides a new fashionable and efficient way to lose weight in 2025. As DanceFitme knows the traditional workout is boring and hard to commit to, you will say goodbye to boring routines and follow us to lose weight efficiently and joyfully.

🌟DanceFitme took more than 2 years to continuously develop programs with the right intensity, music, dance styles, and movements aimed at weight loss and burning calories. Whether you have danced before, DanceFitme will help you lose weight more energetically and efficiently. You never need to be skilled at dance, cause each workout is easy to follow.

🌟Follow the popular music DanceFitme selected and move your body with the dance bit. Just in a song, you can burn about 100 calories while having fun with the pumped-up tunes and energetic moves.

5 MAJOR BENEFITS YOU'LL GET:
- POPULAR QUICK WEIGHT LOSS DANCE STYLES
Aerobics, salsa, Kpop, walking dance, and more specially designed dance &fitness workouts. Over 300+ songs and programs in the DanceFitme app.

- PERSONALIZED DANCE WORKOUTS PLAN
DanceFitme tailors your dance workout plan according to your current body status, weight loss goals, and the areas where you want to improve. With our 4-week dance plan, you are more likely to keep on track. 

- FOR ANY LEVEL
Whether you're a newbie or a pro, you will find suitable programs or workouts in this Dance app with simple and clear instructions. Everyone may be at a different level, the great thing is that you are working out.

- FOR ALL BODY PARTS
Dance workouts are designed by fitness and dance experts to help you achieve your goals. You can select the full body, or specific parts such as abs, butt, back, or legs, to make your practice more targeted.

- AUTOMATED DATA TRACKING
Track your progress to motivate yourself and reach new fitness goals. You can view calories burned and total practice time in DanceFitme. Progress tracking can motivate you to reach new dance fitness levels and get your dream body!

* All payments will be made through your Google Account and may be managed under Account Settings after the initial payment. Subscription payments will automatically renew unless deactivated at least 24 hours before the end of the current cycle. Your account will be charged for renewal at least 24 hours before the end of the current cycle. Any unused portion of your free trial will be forfeited upon payment. Cancellations are incurred by disabling auto-renewal.

CONTACT & INFO
Email: support@dancefit.me
Privacy Policy: https://www.dancefit.me/privacy-policy.html
Terms of Use Agreement: https://www.dancefit.me/terms-of-use.html

FOLLOW US
Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/profile.php?id=100081953393070
Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/dancefitme

high.title: Clear text traffic is Enabled For App
high.description:
[android:usesCleartextTraffic=true]
The app intends to use cleartext network traffic, such as cleartext HTTP, FTP stacks, DownloadManager, and MediaPlayer. The default value for apps that target API level 27 or lower is "true". Apps that target API level 28 or higher default to "false". The key reason for avoiding cleartext traffic is the lack of confidentiality, authenticity, and protections against tampering; a network attacker can eavesdrop on transmitted data and also modify it without being detected.

hotspot.title: Found 9 critical permission(s)
hotspot.description:
Ensure that these permissions are required by the application.

android.permission.POST_NOTIFICATIONS (dangerous): allows an app to post notifications. - Allows an app to post notifications

android.permission.READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE (dangerous): read external storage contents - Allows an application to read from external storage.

android.permission.READ_MEDIA_IMAGES (dangerous): allows reading image files from external storage. - Allows an application to read image files from external storage.

android.permission.CAMERA (dangerous): take pictures and videos - Allows application to take pictures and videos with the camera. This allows the application to collect images that the camera is seeing at any time.

android.permission.READ_MEDIA_VISUAL_USER_SELECTED (dangerous): allows reading user-selected image or video files from external storage. - Allows an application to read image or video files from external storage that a user has selected via the permission prompt photo picker. Apps can check this permission to verify that a user has decided to use the photo picker, instead of granting access to READ_MEDIA_IMAGES or READ_MEDIA_VIDEO . It does not prevent apps from accessing the standard photo picker manually. This permission should be requested alongside READ_MEDIA_IMAGES and/or READ_MEDIA_VIDEO , depending on which type of media is desired.

android.permission.READ_CALENDAR (dangerous): read calendar events - Allows an application to read all of the calendar events stored on your phone. Malicious applications can use this to send your calendar events to other people.

android.permission.WRITE_CALENDAR (dangerous): add or modify calendar events and send emails to guests - Allows an application to add or change the events on your calendar, which may send emails to guests. Malicious applications can use this to erase or modify your calendar events or to send emails to guests.

android.permission.WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE (dangerous): read/modify/delete external storage contents - Allows an application to write to external storage.

android.permission.READ_PHONE_STATE (dangerous): read phone state and identity - Allows the application to access the phone features of the device. An application with this permission can determine the phone number and serial number of this phone, whether a call is active, the number that call is connected to and so on.
